cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning algorithms and their limitations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on learning optimal control in complex environments suggests robotics (cs.RO) as another likely sub-category. The use of simulated environments and the creation of a new environment for testing also suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for image processing in the simulated environment suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a potential sub-category.
